15/01/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador Lawrence Butler has left the post of principal deputy high representative in BiH, to take an unspecified new job in Washington, according to a press release from the Office of High Representative (OHR) on Friday (January 12th). Butler has been in BiH since March 2005. 
In other news, High Representative Christian Schwarz-Schilling is visiting Paris on Monday and travels to Brussels on Tuesday. The focus of the talks is the planned closure of the OHR later this year and its transformation into a EU envoy office. (OHR Sources, RTRS - 14/01/07; Dnevni avaz - 13/01/07; OHR Sources - 12/01/07)
